WEBVTT

00:09.470 --> 00:10.990
Taxi, taxi!

00:11.340 --> 00:12.520
Come on.

00:12.680 --> 00:14.090
It's freezing.

00:14.090 --> 00:15.629
Yeah, it is cold out here.

00:15.630 --> 00:17.009
That's all right. we'll get one.

00:17.010 --> 00:17.909
I'm good at getting cabs.

00:17.910 --> 00:20.090
I'm kinda like the cab whisperer.

00:21.220 --> 00:22.699
That's a nice blazer.

00:22.700 --> 00:24.179
Thank you very much.

00:24.180 --> 00:26.149
It's a gift from, uh-- well, from me.

00:26.150 --> 00:27.799
I wish I'd taken the lining out of it, though.

00:27.800 --> 00:29.329
Sometimes it gets really hot.

00:29.330 --> 00:30.580
Really?

00:33.510 --> 00:34.509
You're shivering.

00:34.510 --> 00:35.409
You noticed.

00:35.410 --> 00:37.729
Well, I notice everything. thank you.

00:37.730 --> 00:39.159
That's my job. I'm a good cop.

00:39.160 --> 00:40.649
Oh, oh, there's a taxi!

00:40.650 --> 00:41.069
There's one. there's one.

00:41.070 --> 00:43.960
Right, right. hey! taxi, taxi!

00:44.080 --> 00:45.320
Taxi!

00:48.050 --> 00:50.420
We got it, we got it, we got it.

00:51.340 --> 00:52.990
Thanks for waiting, man.

00:53.440 --> 00:56.680
Uh, 88 underhill avenue, please.

00:59.980 --> 01:01.220
You're my hero.

01:01.430 --> 01:02.919
Do you want your coat back?

01:02.920 --> 01:05.670
Uh, no, why don't you keep it. I'll get it in the morning.

01:06.150 --> 01:07.679
You're pretty sure of yourself, huh?

01:07.680 --> 01:09.549
Uh, well, I am a cop.

01:09.550 --> 01:11.139
I read the situation.

01:11.140 --> 01:12.149
It's all in the details.

01:12.150 --> 01:16.280
Noticing all those little things that other people miss.

01:16.360 --> 01:17.550
For example,

01:18.420 --> 01:20.550
You usually wear glasses.

01:21.470 --> 01:23.470
I saw you squinting at the menu.

01:24.180 --> 01:25.399
You're pretty good.

01:25.400 --> 01:26.219
Yeah...

01:26.220 --> 01:28.680
Well, I've been doing it for years.

01:28.840 --> 01:30.809
It's second nature by now.

01:30.810 --> 01:32.230
We're not moving.

01:32.850 --> 01:34.710
Randy, oh my god!

01:40.680 --> 01:42.350
It's a jungle out there

01:43.180 --> 01:46.720
Disorder and confusion everywhere

01:47.800 --> 01:49.800
No one seems to care

01:49.970 --> 01:50.900
Well I do

01:50.980 --> 01:53.800
Hey, who's in charge here?

01:54.030 --> 01:56.230
It's a jungle out there

01:57.880 --> 02:00.650
Poison in the very air we breathe

02:01.060 --> 02:03.510
Do you know what's in the water that you drink?

02:03.510 --> 02:07.490
Well I do, and it's amazing

02:07.880 --> 02:10.949
People think I'm crazy, 'cause I worry all the time

02:11.280 --> 02:13.850
If you paid attention, you'd be worried too

02:14.580 --> 02:15.790
You better pay attention

02:15.790 --> 02:22.130
Or this world we love so much might just kill you

02:22.640 --> 02:26.440
I could be wrong now, but I don't think so

02:26.760 --> 02:28.420
It's a jungle out there

02:29.000 --> 02:31.420
It's a jungle out there

02:35.720 --> 02:37.149
Let's meet our victim.

02:37.150 --> 02:39.039
He was a cab driver

02:39.040 --> 02:40.759
Named drazen mirko.

02:40.760 --> 02:42.459
Hey, Randy, does he look familiar?

02:42.460 --> 02:43.769
I was in the backseat.

02:43.770 --> 02:45.399
Mckiernan, what do you got?

02:45.400 --> 02:47.889
Not much. he got his hack license...

02:47.890 --> 02:49.369
About six years ago.

02:49.370 --> 02:51.839
Kept to himself, no known family.

02:51.840 --> 02:53.879
And we're still trying to track down his immigration papers.

02:53.880 --> 02:56.549
The coroner puts the time of death around 9:20.

02:56.550 --> 02:59.149
Multiple puncture wounds from an antique hat pin.

02:59.150 --> 03:00.380
A hat pin?

03:00.620 --> 03:01.539
Can I see that?

03:01.540 --> 03:03.719
So, we're looking for a woman...

03:03.720 --> 03:05.099
That's a start.

03:05.100 --> 03:06.979
Oh, your "l" is a little crooked, there.

03:06.980 --> 03:07.609
No, it's not.

03:07.610 --> 03:08.990
Yes, it is.

03:10.560 --> 03:11.960
It really is.

03:12.650 --> 03:14.920
It's hanging down on the bottom there.

03:19.070 --> 03:20.589
Yeah, it's still a little off.

03:20.590 --> 03:21.780
Now it's... Monk!

03:22.040 --> 03:23.709
This is a homicide task force.

03:23.710 --> 03:24.639
You want me to run downstairs

03:24.640 --> 03:25.569
And get a t-square

03:25.570 --> 03:27.459
So all the letters are even?

03:27.460 --> 03:28.699
It doesn't have to be you necessarily.

03:28.700 --> 03:30.540
You could send... Monk!

03:31.580 --> 03:32.769
Could we move on?

03:32.770 --> 03:34.970
So what is this, a family crest?

03:35.060 --> 03:35.979
Yeah, yeah. something like that.

03:35.980 --> 03:38.470
We're still working on it.

03:38.720 --> 03:40.259
Are there any witnesses?

03:40.260 --> 03:42.049
Randy was there, so...

03:42.050 --> 03:44.209
No, there weren't any witnesses.

03:44.210 --> 03:46.469
I wasn't in cop mode. I was in date mode.

03:46.470 --> 03:47.989
We found this in the cab.

03:47.990 --> 03:49.129
It's got a design on it.

03:49.130 --> 03:50.619
Could be an invitation or something.

03:50.620 --> 03:52.299
And we found this

03:52.300 --> 03:53.319
Under the backseat.

03:53.320 --> 03:54.599
There's blood splatter on it.

03:54.600 --> 03:56.510
We think the killer was wearing it.

03:56.660 --> 03:58.349
A charm bracelet.

03:58.350 --> 04:00.180
Trudy had one of these.

04:00.490 --> 04:04.139
Usually, these aren't just decorative.

04:04.140 --> 04:05.829
Each one of these little charms

04:05.830 --> 04:07.349
Could mean something.

04:07.350 --> 04:08.219
"l.z."

04:08.220 --> 04:09.659
Probably her initials.

04:09.660 --> 04:11.549
L.z. that's good.

04:11.550 --> 04:13.629
There can't be a lot of zs out there.

04:13.630 --> 04:14.309
Ballet slippers.

04:14.310 --> 04:16.469
Maybe she's a dancer or used to be.

04:16.470 --> 04:17.709
Yeah, that's good.

04:17.709 --> 04:19.579
There's a man with a beard.

04:19.610 --> 04:21.159
Looks like santa claus.

04:21.160 --> 04:23.029
Maybe she likes christmas!

04:23.030 --> 04:25.219
I'm not going to write down that she likes christmas.

04:25.220 --> 04:26.499
He is carrying something,

04:26.500 --> 04:28.699
Could be St. Christopher.

04:28.700 --> 04:29.349
He's the patron saint

04:29.350 --> 04:31.140
Of travelers.

04:31.190 --> 04:32.290
Okay.

04:32.450 --> 04:34.210
Likes to travel.

04:34.910 --> 04:36.029
What is that? a lion?

04:36.030 --> 04:38.349
Zoo, zoo, zoo, zoo...zookeeper!

04:38.350 --> 04:40.279
A traveling, dancing zookeeper.

04:40.280 --> 04:42.229
This is not a game show, Randy.

04:42.230 --> 04:42.839
Well, it could be...

04:42.840 --> 04:45.539
An astrological sign. so she's a leo.

04:45.540 --> 04:47.209
A leo. what is that?

04:47.210 --> 04:48.549
Looks like a ruby! yeah.

04:48.550 --> 04:49.769
Rubies, so that's jewelry.

04:49.770 --> 04:50.649
She makes jewelry.

04:50.650 --> 04:51.980
She's a dancing

04:52.000 --> 04:54.399
Zookeeper's daughter who makes jewelry!

04:54.400 --> 04:55.699
Okay! I'm making an announcement.

04:55.700 --> 04:57.419
If our suspect turns out to be

04:57.420 --> 04:59.569
A dancing zookeeper's daughter who makes jewelry,

04:59.570 --> 05:00.840
I'm gonna retire.

05:00.910 --> 05:02.879
Well, it could be a birthstone, right?

05:02.880 --> 05:04.190
What is ruby?

05:04.420 --> 05:05.259
Uh, my mom wears one.

05:05.260 --> 05:06.809
A ruby is july.

05:06.810 --> 05:08.299
If she's a leo that was born in july,

05:08.300 --> 05:10.389
That narrows it down to nine days

05:10.390 --> 05:12.919
Between july 23rd and the 31st.

05:12.920 --> 05:14.009
Alright, here's what we know.

05:14.010 --> 05:16.990
We're looking for a woman whose initials are l.z.,

05:17.000 --> 05:18.510
Maybe she's a dancer. She likes to travel 

05:18.510 --> 05:20.350
Or works with people who travel,

05:20.400 --> 05:21.189
And she was born between

05:21.190 --> 05:23.860
July 23rd and july 31st.

05:24.320 --> 05:25.930
I can't think of anyone.

05:27.600 --> 05:29.119
I thought maybe we'd use the computer

05:29.120 --> 05:30.620
For this one, Randy.

05:31.110 --> 05:32.300
That's a good idea.

05:37.400 --> 05:38.509
Sanchez and Mckiernan

05:38.510 --> 05:40.910
Are checking out the woman in sausalito.

05:41.290 --> 05:42.429
The other one works here.

05:42.430 --> 05:46.150
Her name is Leyla Zlatavich.

05:46.300 --> 05:48.010
You got that dmv photo?

05:48.010 --> 05:49.430
These poor people!

05:49.770 --> 05:52.219
They're all refugees... from Zemenia.

05:52.220 --> 05:53.539
Are they still fighting over there?

05:53.540 --> 05:55.409
They haven't stopped fighting for 600 years.

05:55.410 --> 05:58.279
These are the lucky ones; these people got out.

05:58.280 --> 05:59.830
Captain, over there.

06:04.260 --> 06:05.729
We found you a house.

06:07.990 --> 06:09.330
No, no, no.

06:09.540 --> 06:11.389
No room, a house

06:11.390 --> 06:13.129
With a backyard and a garden.

06:13.130 --> 06:14.420
Your own garden!

06:14.960 --> 06:17.879
No, no, no. everything is paid for.

06:17.880 --> 06:20.839
All we have to do now is fill out some residency papers.

06:20.840 --> 06:23.270
So you come with me? please.

06:25.470 --> 06:27.130
Please, come.

06:31.300 --> 06:32.660
She's beautiful.

06:33.410 --> 06:35.089
Hmm, like mother theresa.

06:35.090 --> 06:36.270
Only hotter.

06:36.330 --> 06:37.460
"only hotter"?

06:37.600 --> 06:39.510
You're gonna get hit by lightning.

06:39.660 --> 06:41.090
She didn't do it.

06:42.450 --> 06:43.189
How do you know that?

06:43.190 --> 06:45.110
We haven't even talked to her yet.

06:46.370 --> 06:47.249
This is Disher.

06:47.250 --> 06:48.680
Captain, it's Sanchez.

